# Player Events (FULL GUIDE)

## Step 1: CODE

```java
@EventHandler
public void onJoin(PlayerJoinEvent event) {
    Player player = event.getPlayer();
    player.sendMessage("Hello " + player.getName());
}
```

---

## Step 2: BREAKDOWN

Player player = event.getPlayer();
→ store player for reuse

getName()
→ returns username

---

## Quit Event

```java
@EventHandler
public void onQuit(PlayerQuitEvent event) {
    System.out.println(event.getPlayer().getName() + " left");
}
```

---

## Step 3: WHAT HAPPENS

Join → message sent
Leave → console log printed

---

## Step 4: REAL DEV TIP

Store player in variable instead of repeating:

❌ event.getPlayer().getName() multiple times

✅ Player player = event.getPlayer();

---

## Mini Challenge
Send title instead of chat message
